    <p>LMNT has built its reputation on a single principle: most electrolyte products do not contain enough sodium. They are correct. The majority of electrolyte gummies and drinks provide 50-150mg sodium per serving — insufficient to meaningfully replace the 500-1,500mg lost per liter of sweat. LMNT's 250mg sodium per serving, combined with potassium and magnesium, delivers a mineral profile that actually matches real-world sweat losses. The zero-sugar formulation avoids unnecessary carbohydrates for athletes on low-carb or ketogenic protocols.</p>

